</table><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Is there still=C2=A0gardening leave? Y=
esterday, the US Federal Trade Commission voted to <a href=3D"https://link.=
mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/35147391.257345/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuZnRjLmdvdi=
9uZXdzLWV2ZW50cy9uZXdzL3ByZXNzLXJlbGVhc2VzLzIwMjQvMDQvZnRjLWFubm91bmNlcy1yd=
WxlLWJhbm5pbmctbm9uY29tcGV0ZQ/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB8b99123e" itemprop=
=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #0=
00000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-b=
ottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">=
ban employee noncompete agreements</a> in the US.<a class=3D"footnote-index=
" href=3D"#footnote-1" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !impo=
rtant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-botto=
m-style: none !important; background-color: transparent !important; display=
: inline-block;">
<span>[1]</span>
</a>=C2=A0Future noncompetes are banned; existing noncompetes are enforceab=
le only for senior executives.<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote=
-2" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-botto=
m-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !impo=
rtant; background-color: transparent !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[2]</span>
</a>=C2=A0The rule goes into effect in six months, and <a href=3D"https://l=
ink.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/35147391.257345/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb2=
1iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjQtMDQtMjMvZnRjLXRvLWlzc3VlLW5vbi1jb21wZ=
XRlLWJhbi1hcy1jaGFtYmVyLWxhd3N1aXQtbG9vbXM_Y21waWQ9QkJEMDQyNDI0X01PTkVZU1RV=
RkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjQwNDI=
0JnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB9f15c05d" itempr=
op=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: =
#000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border=
-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;=
">there will definitely be lawsuits</a> to block it.=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"m=
argin: 16px 0;">In <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click=
/35147391.257345/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuZnRjLmdvdi9zeXN0ZW0vZmlsZXMvZnRjX2dvdi9wZG=
Yvbm9uY29tcGV0ZS1ydWxlLnBkZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBf5f5eb0b" itemprop=3D=
"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #0000=
00; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bott=
om-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">the=
 final rule document</a>, the FTC notes that =E2=80=9Cemployers subject eve=
n middle-income and low-wage workers to noncompetes on a widespread basis,=
=E2=80=9D but of course noncompetes are also common for high-income workers=
 in the financial industry. There, noncompetes are not <em>entirely </em>a =
bad thing for workers. =E2=80=9CAll I know is power-washing and these busin=
ess owners all want me to sign a noncompete clause,=E2=80=9D <a href=3D"htt=
ps://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/35147391.257345/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cu=
ZnRjLmdvdi9zeXN0ZW0vZmlsZXMvZnRjX2dvdi9wZGYvbm9uY29tcGV0ZS1ydWxlLnBkZg/607f=
07ceef4b8524a319a23cCf5f5eb0b" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscop=
e" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !import=
ant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-=
style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">says a power-washer</a> cited by the=
 FTC. =E2=80=9CIt=E2=80=99s one big circle of wealthy business owners keepi=
ng the little man down.=E2=80=9D But on the <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bl=
oombergbusiness.com/click/35147391.257345/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cucmVkZGl0LmNvbS9yL=
3F1YW50L2NvbW1lbnRzLzFjYmNicXEvZnRjX3J1bGVfbm9uY29tcGV0ZXMvP3NoYXJlX2lkPVdm=
QXhlZ3pNMFhOTjUtWE0tc1Q4QiZ1dG1fY29udGVudD0yJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09aW9zX2FwcCZ1dG1=
fbmFtZT1pb3Njc3MmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1zaGFyZSZ1dG1fdGVybT0x/607f07ceef4b8524a319a=
23cBdd63f5ff" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_bla=
nk" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-botto=
m-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; bac=
kground-color: #ccc;">r/quant Reddit board</a>=C2=A0feelings are mixed, and=
 you can find posts saying <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.c=
om/click/35147391.257345/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cucmVkZGl0LmNvbS9yL3F1YW50L2NvbW1lbn=
RzLzFjYmNicXEvY29tbWVudC9sMHlleG91Lw/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB1bab114c" ite=
mprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"colo=
r: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; bor=
der-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #c=
cc;">things like</a>=C2=A0=E2=80=9Cwould suck if this means no garden leave=
 is available anymore.=E2=80=9D In the financial industry, there is a commo=
n norm that, if you leave a job, you are not allowed to work for a competit=
or for some period of months or years, during which you are still paid by y=
our old employer. This makes it harder for you to get a new job and=C2=A0re=
duces your negotiating leverage at your current job, and if you=C2=A0<em>do=
=C2=A0</em>leave, the enforced time off devalues your skills and holds back=
 your career. On the other hand: year-long vacation! There are probably som=
e people who structure their financial careers around <a href=3D"https://li=
nk.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/35147391.257345/aHR0cHM6Ly90d2l0dGVyLmN=
vbS9CeXJuZUhvYmFydC9zdGF0dXMvMTc0NTE0OTUzOTY3NjIxNzM1OA/607f07ceef4b8524a31=
9a23cB295d9993" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_b=
lank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bot=
tom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; b=
ackground-color: #ccc;">maximizing gardening leave</a>. Did the FTC end tha=
t?</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I don=E2=80=99t think so, though it=E2=
=80=99s a little unclear. There are roughly four ways that financial firms =
typically deter people from leaving for competitors:</p><ol style=3D"list-s=
tyle-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;">=09<li style=3D"ma=
rgin-bottom: 5px;">Noncompetes: When you start your job, you sign a contrac=
t promising not to work for a competitor for, say, six months<a class=3D"fo=
otnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-3" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration=
