</em>It just writes down a list of stocks. And BlackRock can deny any respo=
nsibility for these investments, because it just runs passive index funds: =
It just invests in a list of stocks somebody else (MSCI) wrote down. =E2=80=
=9COne attraction of index investing is that nobody is responsible for any =
investing decisions,=E2=80=9D I wrote. The decision to =E2=80=9Cchannel Ame=
ricans=E2=80=99 savings into the companies in question=E2=80=9D is an emerg=
ent property of the index-fund system; nobody actually made that decision.=
=C2=A0Congress wants someone to yell at, but there=E2=80=99s nobody to yell=
 at.</p><table class=3D"header" width=3D"100%" border=3D"0" cellspacing=3D"=
