</table><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">There is a form of argument, in crypto=
, that is like: =E2=80=9CThis token costs $10. If you buy a token and hold =
it, it will turn into six tokens. If each of those tokens is still worth $1=
0, you will have turned $10 into $60.=E2=80=9D This had an <a href=3D"https=
://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/35147391.257345/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuY2=
