=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: =
none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; bo=
rder-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">by turning each=C2=A0rur=
al home into six rural homes</a>:</p><blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0=
;">It seemed to be a great deal at the time: Swap an aging townhouse and a =
small piece of farmland for five apartments and two stores.</p><p style=3D"=
margin: 16px 0;">Bella Zhao=E2=80=99s family grabbed that offer in 2009, wh=
en property developers led by Wanda Group moved into their sparse, snow-cap=
ped village in China=E2=80=99s northeastern Jilin province. Wanda planned t=
o spend $2.8 billion to turn the area into a high-end resort replete with s=
ki slopes, golf courses, hunting spots and five-star hotels. The developer =
offered locals a large number of new apartments in town in exchange for the=
ir old homes, creating a village of property tycoons almost overnight.</p><=
p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CI was so happy then,=E2=80=9D said Zha=
o, who was a teenager at the time and later inherited the properties.=C2=A0=
</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Now, all five of her apartments sit empty.=
 Only one of the stores has a tenant. =E2=80=A6</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px=
 0;">The market is facing a simple economic problem: too many sellers, and =
too few buyers. Making matters worse, villagers who traded their homes with=
 developers, often for several new apartments, are adding to the wall of po=
tential supply, said Liu Yuan, head of property research at Centaline.</p><=
p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CIt is impossible to sell at a decent p=
rice,=E2=80=9D said a homeowner in Nanjing, who owns eight properties with =
her husband and parents, five of which were compensation for relocating.</p=
></blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">On the one hand, right, if you m=
ultiply the supply of apartments by six, and change nothing else (populatio=
n, tourism, etc.), then the price of those apartments is going to go down. =
On the other hand, now you have more room? =E2=80=9CPerhaps two of the apar=
tments will be occupied by his relatives,=E2=80=9D says a guy in Henan who =
traded a house for six apartments, though=C2=A0=E2=80=9Cthe rest will sit e=
mpty.=E2=80=9D Possibly that is an increase in wealth?</p><table class=3D"h=
